1.create project
django-admin startproject crudexample

2.create app inside project

crudexample >> django-admin startapp employee

3.create virtual environment
 >> virtualenv venv -p python
 >> source venv/bin/activate


4. this example uses db.sqlite3 , below code uses mysql
database setup, configure in settings.py
    DATABASES = {  
        'default': {  
            'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.mysql',  
            'NAME': 'djangodb',  
            'USER':'root',  
            'PASSWORD':'root',  
            'HOST':'localhost',  
            'PORT':'3306'  
        }  
    }  


5.create class employee in models.py

6.create class employee form in forms.py (employee app)

7.write functions in views.py to handle crud

8.create html files in templates

9.add app in installed app list under settings.py

10.add template path in settins.py

11.creating db and table
 python3 manage.py makemigrations
 python3 manage.py migrate


note: no css files
